                            <comment id="12655504" author="noble.paul" created="Thu, 11 Dec 2008 04:50:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;untested.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12655884" author="noble.paul" created="Fri, 12 Dec 2008 04:52:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;it had an obvious bug. But still untested&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12655948" author="akshay" created="Fri, 12 Dec 2008 10:11:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch with minor bug fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12656276" author="noble.paul" created="Sat, 13 Dec 2008 12:07:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;allows copying a file in many names as follows&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&amp;lt;str name=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;confFiles&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;slave_solrconfig.xml,slave_solrconfig.xml:solrconfig.xml&amp;lt;/str&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12656306" author="shalinmangar" created="Sat, 13 Dec 2008 17:10:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Noble, since we use comma as separator for multiple files, did you mean this instead?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-xml&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;str name=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;confFiles&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;slave_solrconfig.xml:slave_solrconfig.xml,slave_solrconfig.xml:solrconfig.xml&lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;/str&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will make it possible to have config replication while allowing setting up repeaters for replicating across different data centers.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12656379" author="noble.paul" created="Sun, 14 Dec 2008 11:22:19 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Noble, since we use comma as separator for multiple files, did you mean this instead? &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;nope . Both the configurations will have same effect. If name and alias are same no need to repeat it. I mean that is the default behavior where the colon is not used. &lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12656425" author="shalinmangar" created="Sun, 14 Dec 2008 18:05:45 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;If name and alias are same no need to repeat it. I mean that is the default behavior where the colon is not used. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ok I see. Sorry for the confusion.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need a test for this. Though the change is small, the feature is very important. I&apos;ll give a patch with a test.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12656907" author="akshay" created="Tue, 16 Dec 2008 07:32:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch with test case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12656929" author="akshay" created="Tue, 16 Dec 2008 10:07:46 +0000"  >&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Patch with test case.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Removed unused parts from solrconfig.xml and schema.xml in the test files.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Few missing null pointer checks added.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12656947" author="shalinmangar" created="Tue, 16 Dec 2008 10:42:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is looking good, thanks Akshay!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll commit this in a day or two.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12657316" author="shalinmangar" created="Wed, 17 Dec 2008 09:19:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 727319.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks Akshay and Noble!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12775558" author="gsingers" created="Tue, 10 Nov 2009 15:51:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bulk close for Solr 1.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12885543" author="grahamp" created="Tue, 6 Jul 2010 14:42:43 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;We don&apos;t have that problem, because we use solrcore.properties, containing:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;enable.master=true&lt;br/&gt;
enable.slave=false&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(or visa versa on the slaves)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then the same solrconfig can be used on both (where solr.master is defined in solr.xml above the cores:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  &amp;lt;requestHandler name=&quot;/replication&quot; class=&quot;solr.ReplicationHandler&quot; &amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;lst name=&quot;master&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;str name=&quot;enable&quot;&amp;gt;$&lt;/p&gt;
{enable.master:false}
&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;/str&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;str name=&quot;replicateAfter&quot;&amp;gt;commit&amp;lt;/str&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;str name=&quot;replicateAfter&quot;&amp;gt;startup&amp;lt;/str&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;/lst&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;lst name=&quot;slave&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;str name=&quot;enable&quot;&amp;gt;$&lt;/p&gt;
{enable.slave:false}
&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;/str&amp;gt; &lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;str name=&quot;masterUrl&quot;&amp;gt;$&lt;/p&gt;
{solr.master}
&lt;p&gt;/$&lt;/p&gt;
{solr.core.name}
&lt;p&gt;/replication&amp;lt;/str&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;str name=&quot;pollInterval&quot;&amp;gt;00:00:60&amp;lt;/str&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;/lst&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/requestHandler&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
